  {
    "index": 3,
    "hash": "Jh5yRi1CAMPIZMw0ajYZqwMDtf4=",
    "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:41.000Z",
    "action": {
      "type": "SET_CONTENT",
      "input": {
        "content": "## Push sequence (Create to Sync to Swarm)\n\nTriggered by `SyncManager.updateOutbox()` when new ordinals appear in `operation_index_operations`.\n\n`SwarmChannel.handleOutboxAdded()` then, per SyncOperation:\n\n1. Serialize `OperationWithContext[]` to JSON.\n2. Encrypt with AES-256-GCM using a wallet-derived key.\n3. Upload ciphertext to `/bytes` \u2014 receive content reference (hash).\n4. Read existing document manifest from feed (or create new).\n5. Append the batch reference (with scope and index range) to the manifest.\n6. Write updated manifest as a SOC (single-owner chunk) to the doc feed.\n7. Call `syncOp.executed()` so the sync cursor advances.\n\n### Special case: drive documents\n\nWhen `documentType === \"powerhouse/document-drive\"`:\n\n- `ManifestManager.updateDriveManifest()` reads drive state from the reactor and writes the docs plus folders index to the drive manifest feed.\n- `ManifestManager.ensureDriveInUserManifest()` updates the user manifest with a drive entry, building the discovery index used for recovery.\n\n### Example operation set\n\nCreating `PushPullDrive` with one doc, one folder, one nested doc generates: `CREATE_DOCUMENT`, `UPGRADE_DOCUMENT`, `ADD_FILE`, `ADD_FOLDER`, `ADD_FILE (parentFolder=folder)`, `MOVE_NODE`.",
        "updatedAt": "2026-05-13T13:00:41.000Z"
      },
      "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:41.000Z"
    }
  },
